'''Dina Blond''' (1 March 1887 - 1985) was a prominent member of the [[General Jewish Labour Bund in Poland|Jewish Labour Bund in Poland]] and a prolific [[Yiddish]] translator.
She was born Shayne-Feygl Szapiro in [[Vilna]],<ref>The Jewish Women's Archive Encyclopedia, {{cite web|url=https://jwa.org/encyclopedia/article/blond-dina|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180217183205/https://jwa.org/encyclopedia/article/blond-dina|archivedate=17 February 2018 |deadurl=no||title=Dina Blond|author=Gertrud Pickhan|accessdate=17 February 2018}}</ref> then a part of the [[Russian Empire]].
In the mid-1920s Blond became chairwoman of the Bund's women's organisation, the [[Yidisher Arbeter Froy]] (YAF). She was also editor of the women's page of the party newspaper, ''[[Folkstsaytung]]''.<ref>YIVO Archives {{cite web|url=http://www.yivoarchives.org/index.php?p=collections/controlcard&id=34161|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180217183402/http://www.yivoarchives.org/index.php?p=collections/controlcard&id=34161|archivedate=17 February 2018 |deadurl=no||title=Dina Blond|accessdate=17 February 2018}}</ref>
